          <p class='first-para'>
            Order. I have already asked for hon. Members' co-operation. I now ask hon. Members to listen patiently to the remainder of the winding-up speech. If any hon. Member feels it necessary to intervene, it is up to the Minister to decide whether to give way. I ask again for the background music to be kept low.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0375P0-04671'>
        <a name='S6CV0375P0_20011121_WH_117'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-alun-michael' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0375P0_20011121_WH_117' title='Link to this speech by Mr Alun Michael' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-alun-michael" title="Mr Alun Michael">Alun Michael</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I am tempted to suggest that Conservative Members simply want to cut the time available for the response.</p><p>
            Those who peddle scare stories are not undermining the Government, but the confidence of those who deserve encouragement and support. Those people desperately need confidence. Let me nail the rural myths. The Government are not trying to shut down British livestock farming; there is no European Union plot to sabotage farming; we are not using foot and mouth to close down large parts of the sheep sector. The Government are committed to viable, vibrant and sustainable British agriculture, which comprises livestock and arable farms.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
