          <p class='first-para'>
            On a point of order, Mr. Benton. I understood that you were in charge of proceedings and
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_113wh' title='Col. 113WH &mdash; HC Deb 21 November 2001 vol 375 c113WH' name='column_113wh' href='#column_113wh' rel='bookmark'>113WH</a>
            that you would call hon. Members to order if necessary. It is not for me to call any hon. Member to order and I should like the Minister to withdraw his rather silly remark.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0375P0-04677'>
        <a name='S6CV0375P0_20011121_WH_123'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-joe-benton' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0375P0_20011121_WH_123' title='Link to this speech by Mr Joe Benton' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
